wikipedia.title: Mikiko
wikipedia.extract:
Mikiko (written: 幹子, 美樹子, 美起子, 美紀子, 美希子 or みきこ in hiragana) is a feminine Japanese given name. Notable people with the name include:

Mikiko Ando (安藤 美希子, born 1992), Japanese weightlifter
Mikiko Enomoto (榎本 充希子, born 1973), Japanese voice actress
Mikiko Hagiwara (萩原 美樹子, born 1970), Japanese women's basketball player
Mikiko Hara (原 美樹子, born 1967), Japanese photographer
Mikiko Kato (加藤 美起子, born 1954), Japanese handball player
Mikiko Miki (三輝 みきこ), Japanese actress
Mikiko Mizuno (水野幹子), known professionally as MIKIKO, Japanese choreographer
Mikiko Ponczeck (born 1984), German-Japanese comic book artist
Mikiko Shiroma (城間 幹子, born 1951), Japanese politician
Mikiko Sone (曽根 幹子, born 1952), Japanese high jumper
Mikiko Takeya (竹屋 美紀子, born 1980), Japanese sprint canoeist
